  "title": "Investment Portfolio Specialist",
  "description": "<p></p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>•\tReview and assess client investment portfolios to understand asset allocation, risk exposure, diversification, and investment time horizons</p><p>•\tIdentify portfolio gaps, concentration issues, or inefficiencies and prepare adjustment points for discussion</p><p>•\tSupport ongoing portfolio reviews as market conditions and client circumstances evolve</p><p>•\tPrepare portfolio summaries, comparisons, and review materials for use in client discussions and follow-ups</p><p>•\tDevelop a strong understanding of portfolio construction principles, asset allocation strategies, and investment decision-making</p><p>•\tBuild familiarity with how investment recommendations are communicated and implemented in client settings</p><p></p><p>Requirements</p><p>•\tDiploma or above in Finance, Business, Accountancy, or related disciplines, 3rd year students and fresh graduates welcome</p><p>•\tStrong interest in investments advisory</p><p>•\tComfortable with professional client-facing discussions</p><p>•\tSelf-motivated, disciplined, and able to operate in a performance-based environment</p><p>•\tPrior experience in investment-related, client-facing, or business development roles is an advantage</p>",
